        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued May 21 at 1:59AM EDT by NWS Blacksburg VA</headline>
        <description>At 159 AM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a cluster of strong
thunderstorms near Keeling, or 7 miles southwest of Ingram, moving
northeast at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Danville...
Eden...
Reidsville...
Martinsville...
South Boston...
Wentworth...
and Mayodan.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
